			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				Yes this is a very sore subject for alot of warriors. And like you said, the uber guilds farm Serv and he dies within 1 hour of poping. Being a 7 day spawn this is very difficult for the &quot;lesser&quot; guilds to try and take him out for their warriors. <br>   <br> I know personally I have worked very hard on my epic and the chances of getting Serv is slim to none. I am on the last 4 pieces I need to complete my epic and I hope to someday weild the Lightsabers. <br> I think SoE really screwed up on the warrior epic. They make the quest damn near impossible to complete, then make the green scale a total bottleneck to get. Like you said, either you get very lucky to get the scale on a raid or you save up 100k to buy it. Asking ungodly amounts of plat for an item being epic or not is totally crazy. But that is the economy that this server. Which is one of the most expensive out there.  <br> Little is going to come out of this thread other then a bunch of peeps that will be looked at as &quot;bitching&quot; about an item.  <br> I agree with you that there needs to be a more fair system to taking out Serv, but there is little chances of that happening. So take it in stride, and maybe you will be fortunate enough to get the scale.  <br> Making the scale no drop....that will help and hinder the warriors as well. You will no longer have to shell out 100k on the scale, but you will have to have the raid force capable of taking Serv out as well. And for alot of us in &quot;lesser&quot; guilds this is going to be a pain as well. Great Catch 22 that we are in <img src="/images/faces/happy.gif" border=0 alt="happy.gif" height=16 hspace=0 width=18 vspace=0>  <br>  <br> Callak Kellrass <br> 51 Warrior of Rallos Zek <br> OOR		

