		<tr valign=top>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				First off you're wrong about uber guilds being the only ones to kill Sev.  Secondly those that do kill him often also need the scale for an epic rather than to sell it.  Being in a large guild also doesn't seal the deal for getting your scale.  He doesn't always drop it and usually larger guilds have other things to do besides epics and members are off doing other things when Sev spawns and you're asking for help. <br>  <br> Another thing that kind of bugs me about this post is the level of those posting.  You're level 51 that's a bit too low to be complaining about not getting to a dragon.  If this dragon is the last piece for your epic you should at least be able to MT the mob that drops it.  Assuming he's the difficulty of the rest of the kunark dragons (correct me if I'm wrong here I've never fought him), an average raid of 51s would be hard pressed to be able to kill him. <br>  <br> Also, you do not need to be in an uber guild to get really good weapons besides your epic.  Ashorty leads great public raids and anyone can join them provided they're willing to take the time they'd spend camping Sev to really xp grind and get to 65.  And if you're not planning on spending the time to do that anytime soon, you probably won't need your epic to hold aggro on high end raids and your snowchipper/wavecrasher/frostie/fleshgrinder whatever will work just fine <img src="/images/faces/wink.gif" border=0 alt="wink.gif" height=16 hspace=0 width=18 vspace=0>  <br>  <br> In conclusion I'd like to add that I totally agree with you that the scale should be no drop.
